PREHEAT oven to 400 degrees F. MELT butter in medium skillet over medium heat; add onion. Cook until lightly browned. Add cream cheese; stir until melted. Remove skillet from heat. Add stuffing; stir to coat with cream cheese. COMBINE beef stroganoff and mushrooms in a large oven-safe skillet. Cover; cook over high for heat 3 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle with stuffing. BAKE for 15 to 18 minutes or until stuffing is lightly browned.